Iraq, Egypt, Yemen - compiled by L. Wells - Hisham Khatib Collection
Khatib, Hisham, Mr.
Wells, Les, Active 1929 - 1938
AD.MC.030_ref158
33 Leaves - 36 gelatin silver photographs
1934 - 1936 Created by officer Les Wells while he served with the Medical Service at the RAF General Hospital in Hinaidi as part of the "British Forces in Iraq" RAF Command and whilst he was stationed in Egypt between 1934 and 1936 - part of the Hisham Khatib Collection. Digital copy only - ref158
Content Description
A photograph album containing 36 gelatin silver prints of sites and people in Iraq and Egypt between 1934 and 1936.
Conditions Governing Use
Any rights (including copyright and related rights to publicity and privacy) held by Dr. Hisham Khatib are maintained by New York University. Permission to publish or reproduce materials in this collection must be secured from repository. Please contact Akkasah at akkasah@nyu.edu
Conditions Governing Access
Materials are open without restrictions.
